The paper proposes a framework for distributed computing that addresses issues of resiliency, security, and privacy. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper focuses on machine learning computations, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel coding scheme, which could also make it relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
